	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">thefox wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">In any case it would be nice to have ways of detecting the clone machines with software, so at least a warning could be displayed to their users. Anybody know any tricks like that?</div>
<br />At first, I'd recommend running Blargg's tests on clones to get some ideas for how to detect them at startup. But there are a few problems: 1. Blargg appears to have left the community for some reason, and 2. the PowerPak is said not to even boot on clones, so only someone who knows how to solder would be able to just buy one and run the existing test suites.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


